rComments: He is very knowledgeable. Very practical class. I am using the materials in my job.

Terrible Professor , He is highly demeaning and very full of himself. Minimal in class support and the feedback was often missing and after class support was non existent. If you asked questions, you were made to feel stupid . Terrible teaching methods and class feedback was never taken on board regarding deadlines and class material .

The problem with Telfer Finance is that most of the profs graduated from a not-so-good business school, and yet they demand their students to be on par with Wharton people. The course is not hard, but this prof skips the basic knowledge extremely fast and jumps to master level questions. If u r really interested in financial modelling, self study.

The professor is cocky and full of himself. He hinted at the fact that the class was stupid multiple times throughout the term. He put too many complex problems in a short amount of time for both the midterm and the final exam. The class itself is not difficult, just keep in mind that he will make you feel bad throughout the term.

I think the other students were harsh on their reviews for this course. Yes, its very heavily based on excel, and yes there was not enough time for the midterm. However, the prof did give us extra time for the exams, and all the exam and assignment questions were very similar (if not exactly the same) as the practice questions. Overall, not bad!

Do not TAKE this class. I repeat. Do not TAKE this class. This is a newly designed finance course with tons of flaws and you will have no reference or other materials to help you do better in this class. Midterm is long, and you only have 45 mins to complete it, which is a mission impossible. Avoid this course and this prof. Go take better classes.

This prof is the exact epitome of what's wrong with Telfer's finance major. The course has good intentions of teaching you how to use EXCEL to craft financial models to solve problems, but the execution of this new course is a complete shambles. Assignments are so difficult that you will question if you forget to take another prerequisite class.
Avoid this course if you can. So unorganized and the professor makes the midterm and final too long to complete in the allotted time.

This course is a total disaster this semester. The class involves using excel, so hand-on learning is very important but the current situation will leave you confused since the only reference you have is a bunch of YouTube videos. The assignments and exams for this course are horrible, and the prof gives so little time to do them. Instant regrets.

This course demonstrates why Telfer is not a top-tier B school. What were they thinking when they opened a course that wasn't even properly structured? This course has an unbelievable midterm that requires you to solve some complicated financial problems with EXCEL within 45 mins! This course does nothing but drags down my GPA. Please AVOID 3354 .

Do not take this class ESPECIALLY WITH THIS PROF. I repeat. DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS ! or at at least not with this prof. IF YOU have it right now, LEAVE IMMEDIATELY AND RUN ! Good prof, his lectures are not very useful as all the quizzes, tests and final are based on the recommended problems he gives out.

He is a good prof. He will do the best practice exercises in class to prepare the students for the exams. Review and practice those as well as the ones online over and over again for the quizzes and exams. He is also available outside of class hours for extra help and answer questions.
